\subsection{Data Preprocessing}
Data preprocessing is a critical step in any machine learning pipeline, as the 
quality of the input data directly affects model performance 
\citep{zhao2006effective}. The preprocessing steps applied in this project are 
summarised in Figure~\ref{fig:pipeline} and described below.
\\
\\During data cleaning, 108 duplicate records were identified, meaning multiple entries 
existed for the same product on the same date. These were resolved by grouping and 
summing entries by product and date. The data were then aggregated from daily to 
weekly level, using \texttt{week\_start} as the unified time key, and merged with 
the external data sources.
\\
\\Products with fewer than 52 weeks of historical records were excluded from the 
analysis. This step was necessary because sparse, intermittent demand series are 
known to cause significant challenges for standard forecasting models 
\citep{turkmen2021forecasting}. After filtering, 114 products and approximately 
13,579 weekly observation records were retained for modelling.

